article.headline: NDSU 86, SDSU 69
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Ben Woodside and Andre Smith combined for 45 points to help North Dakota State defeat South Dakota State 86-69 Saturday night. The victory gave the Bison (18-8) a series sweep against their cross-border rivals. Woodside, a sophomore point guard, led the way with 23 points. Smith, the lone senior on the NDSU roster, added 22 points, 16 in the first half. The Bison led 36-28 at intermission. Jose Frias topped the Jackrabbits (5-23) with 20 points. Smith's slam dunk about 5 minutes into the game put NDSU ahead for good at 8-7. That also was part of a 12-0 run that gave the Bison a 17-7 lead. NDSU's biggest lead in the first half was 13 points, before the Jackrabbits scored 10 unanswered points to pull within 24-21. The Bison opened the second half by scoring nine straight points, capped by another dunk by Smith to make it 45-28. SDSU could only get within nine points the rest of the way. The second half was marred by five technical fouls, three on SDSU.
